	skos:narrower <http://astrothesaurus.org/uat/1365> , <http://astrothesaurus.org/uat/1101> , <http://astrothesaurus.org/uat/1235> , <http://astrothesaurus.org/uat/1293> , <http://astrothesaurus.org/uat/137> , <http://astrothesaurus.org/uat/138> , <http://astrothesaurus.org/uat/1383> , <http://astrothesaurus.org/uat/784> , <http://astrothesaurus.org/uat/795> , <http://astrothesaurus.org/uat/916> ;
	skos:definition "A qualitative term used to describe a phase in the history of the Universe, from the Big Bang event to the apparition of the first structures (seeds of future galaxies), at a redshift around 30."@en .

