	skos:narrower <http://astrothesaurus.org/uat/940> , <http://astrothesaurus.org/uat/2016> , <http://astrothesaurus.org/uat/17> , <http://astrothesaurus.org/uat/459> , <http://astrothesaurus.org/uat/285> , <http://astrothesaurus.org/uat/416> , <http://astrothesaurus.org/uat/1347> , <http://astrothesaurus.org/uat/1293> , <http://astrothesaurus.org/uat/1298> , <http://astrothesaurus.org/uat/1316> , <http://astrothesaurus.org/uat/391> , <http://astrothesaurus.org/uat/736> , <http://astrothesaurus.org/uat/1570> , <http://astrothesaurus.org/uat/652> , <http://astrothesaurus.org/uat/290> , <http://astrothesaurus.org/uat/456> , <http://astrothesaurus.org/uat/864> , <http://astrothesaurus.org/uat/405> , <http://astrothesaurus.org/uat/429> , <http://astrothesaurus.org/uat/533> , <http://astrothesaurus.org/uat/734> , <http://astrothesaurus.org/uat/789> , <http://astrothesaurus.org/uat/802> , <http://astrothesaurus.org/uat/907> , <http://astrothesaurus.org/uat/978> , <http://astrothesaurus.org/uat/979> , <http://astrothesaurus.org/uat/2176> ;
	skos:related <http://astrothesaurus.org/uat/611> , <http://astrothesaurus.org/uat/582> , <http://astrothesaurus.org/uat/2171> ;
	skos:definition "Generally, a large body of gas, dust, and stars held together by their mutual gravitational attraction and ranging in mass from about 10^6 to 10^13 M_sun. If a galaxy also contains dark matter its mass will be much larger. Galaxies are grouped into three main categories: spiral galaxies, elliptical galaxies, and irregular galaxies."@en .

