	skos:prefLabel "Termination shock"@en ;
	skos:definition "A shock wave inside the heliopause where the supersonic solar wind abruptly slows from an average speed of 500 km s^-1 to subsonic and becomes denser and hotter."@en .

<http://astrothesaurus.org/uat/1691> a rdfs:Resource , skos:Concept ;
